Today marks my completion of my 10th year as a professional tattoo artist. 
I am incredibly humbled and grateful to have had this opportunity. Tattooing has been such a rewarding career for many reasons. But I’ll try not to blabber on too long lol  so I just wanted to Thank each and every person who has giving me the great honor of tattooing them, my fellow Tattooers I have had the privilege of working with and learning from. All of you from DV8 , pretty in ink , reclamare/neon tiger and my own shop, y’all know who you are. Seriously thank you for helping and supporting me through the last 10 years. 
I always told myself once I hit 10 years then I could call myself a true tattoo artist and I would really turn on the heat so I hope you’re ready for these next 10 and beyond! 
Cheers and thank you from the bottom of my heart ❤️

Hey everyone! I wanted to introduce my two apprentices Erica and Rusty! They have already completed 5 months as apprentices and have learned and improved a lot in that time.  Please give them a follow and watch their journey into tattooing! I am excited to see what they will do in this industry with fundamentals and hard work at the core. Trying my best to share my knowledge with respect to the ones who came before us and to the ones who will continue when we are gone.
